snippet.textDisplay:
A little perspective.
Influenza killed about 80,000 people in the 2017-2018 season, according to figures released by the Centers for Disease Control and Prevention. The previous high for a regular flu season, based on analyses dating back more than three decades, was 56,000 deaths.Sep 27, 201856,000 people died of flue between 2011-2012. This is WAY OVERBLOWN at this point. As of April 19, 2019, a total of 186 pediatric deaths had been reported to CDC for Flu during the 2017-2018 season. This number exceeds the previously highest number of flu-associated deaths in children reported during a regular flu season (171 during the 2012-2013 season). Approximately 80% of these deaths occurred in children who had not received a flu vaccination this season. As it does for the numbers of flu cases, doctor’s visits and hospitalizations, CDC also estimates deaths in the United States using mathematical modeling. CDC estimates that from 2010-2011 to 2013-2014, influenza-associated deaths in the United States ranged from a low of 12,000 (during 2011-2012) to a high of 56,000 (during 2012-2013).

IF U LIVE IN CHINA 🇨🇳 please share this message: During this time, with the Wuhan Virus spreading, many ill-informed pet owners are abandoning their pets because they fear their pet could spread the virus to them. In case anyone is nervous that dogs or cats could give them the virus, you can rest assured that is not possible.

There are many different kinds of corona virus. Feline corona virus only affects cats, and cannot be spread to dogs or people. 🐱 Canine corona virus only affects dogs, and cannot be spread to cats or people. 🐶 That is one of the things we vaccinate our pets to protect against: species specific viruses that are very dangerous to our pets, but not to us. Rabies is an exception because it can spread to different species.

This new corona virus was caused by EATING wild animals, likely a bat or a snake.🦇 🐍 It is spread through contact with other humans infected with the virus, not through regular contact with pets. ❤️ 🐶 🐱 ❤️
